Consider a right triangle as shown.  Applying the Pythagorean theorem yields \[(r+s)^2=(r-3s)^2+(r-s)^2 \]Simplifying,  \begin{align*}
r^2+2rs+s^2&=r^2-6rs+9s^2+r^2-2rs+s^2\\
0&=r^2-10rs+9s^2\\
&=(r-9s)(r-s)\\
\end{align*}But we know that $r\neq s$, so the only solution is $r = 9s$; hence $r/s = \boxed{9}.$

